# =============================================================================
# nest-server-starter — Environment Variables
# =============================================================================
# Copy to `.env` and adjust values.
#
# Legend:
#   - Uncommented lines → REQUIRED for a deployed environment (`develop`,
#     `test`, `production`). Missing values fail the server startup.
#   - Commented lines  → OPTIONAL (framework default applies).
#
# Local-only environments (`local`, `ci`, `e2e`) ship public dummy secrets
# and Mailhog defaults in `src/config.env.ts` — they run completely without
# a `.env` file.
#
# Two ways to configure (both supported):
#   1. NSC__-prefixed env vars → auto-merged into the config tree by
#      `getEnvironmentConfig`. Path: `NSC__FOO__BAR` → `config.foo.bar`,
#      single underscore = camelCase boundary.
#      (e.g. `NSC__BETTER_AUTH__SECRET` → `config.betterAuth.secret`)
#   2. Direct env vars (e.g. `CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS`):
#      read explicitly in `src/config.env.ts` for values that need parsing.


# =============================================================================
# Database (required in deployed envs)
# =============================================================================

NSC__MONGOOSE__URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/nest-server-starter-production


# =============================================================================
# URLs (required in deployed envs)
# =============================================================================

# API base URL — used for CORS, Passkey RP ID, email links, OAuth callbacks.
# The frontend/app URL is auto-derived: api.example.com → example.com
NSC__BASE_URL=https://api.example.com

# Frontend/app URL (optional — auto-derived from BASE_URL if unset)
# NSC__APP_URL=https://example.com


# =============================================================================
# Authentication Secrets (required in deployed envs)
# =============================================================================

# Better-Auth secret — signs session cookies + BetterAuth JWTs. Minimum 32 characters.
# Generate with:
#   node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('base64'))"
NSC__BETTER_AUTH__SECRET=CHANGE_ME_generate_32plus_chars_with_node_crypto_randomBytes

# Legacy JWT secrets — ONLY required if a project opts back into Legacy Auth
# endpoints by setting `auth.legacyEndpoints.enabled: true` in src/config.env.ts.
# The starter ships BetterAuth-only; leave unset for new projects.
# Generate with:
#   node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(64).toString('base64'))"
# NSC__JWT__SECRET=CHANGE_ME_generate_64plus_chars_with_node_crypto_randomBytes
# NSC__JWT__REFRESH__SECRET=CHANGE_ME_different_64plus_chars_than_JWT_SECRET


# =============================================================================
# Email — SMTP required in deployed envs, Brevo optional overlay
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SMTP (required — baseline transport for ALL outgoing mail)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Any SMTP provider: AWS SES, SendGrid, Postmark, Mailgun, self-hosted Postfix.
# Handles all auth flows and custom app emails.
NSC__EMAIL__DEFAULT_SENDER__EMAIL=noreply@example.com
NSC__EMAIL__SMTP__HOST=smtp.example.com
NSC__EMAIL__SMTP__AUTH__USER=smtp-user
NSC__EMAIL__SMTP__AUTH__PASS=smtp-password
# NSC__EMAIL__DEFAULT_SENDER__NAME=Nest Server Starter   # default: project brand name
# SMTP_PORT=587                                          # default: 587
# SMTP_SECURE=true                                       # default: true (set "false" for STARTTLS on :587)

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Brevo Transactional API (optional overlay for template-based mails)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Brevo (ex-Sendinblue) sends via HTTPS with server-side templates.
# Runs IN PARALLEL to SMTP — only used when a module references a
# `brevoTemplateId` (e.g. `betterAuth.emailVerification.brevoTemplateId`).
# All other mails still flow through the SMTP transport above.
# Get an API key at https://app.brevo.com/settings/keys/api
# BREVO_API_KEY=xkeysib-your-brevo-api-key


# =============================================================================
# CORS (optional — origins auto-derived from BASE_URL + APP_URL)
# =============================================================================

# Additional allowed origins (comma-separated, merged with APP_URL + BASE_URL).
# CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://admin.example.com,https://partner.example.com


# =============================================================================
# Feature Toggles (optional — sensible defaults apply)
# =============================================================================

# Two-Factor Authentication app name — shown in Authenticator apps (TOTP issuer).
# Default: project brand name from src/config.env.ts.
# TWO_FACTOR_APP_NAME=My App


# =============================================================================
# Social Login (optional — BetterAuth OAuth providers)
# =============================================================================
# Set both ID and SECRET to activate a provider.

# NSC__BETTER_AUTH__SOCIAL_PROVIDERS__GOOGLE__CLIENT_ID=
# NSC__BETTER_AUTH__SOCIAL_PROVIDERS__GOOGLE__CLIENT_SECRET=
# NSC__BETTER_AUTH__SOCIAL_PROVIDERS__GITHUB__CLIENT_ID=
# NSC__BETTER_AUTH__SOCIAL_PROVIDERS__GITHUB__CLIENT_SECRET=


# =============================================================================
# Initial Admin (optional — first deployment only; remove after setup)
# =============================================================================
# Creates a single admin user on first startup if the user collection is empty.

# NSC__SYSTEM_SETUP__INITIAL_ADMIN__EMAIL=admin@example.com
# NSC__SYSTEM_SETUP__INITIAL_ADMIN__PASSWORD=YourSecurePassword123!
# NSC__SYSTEM_SETUP__INITIAL_ADMIN__NAME=Admin
